Bates Courier - GitHub Pages Deployment Instructions
----------------------------------------------------

1. Sign up for a free GitHub account if you don’t have one:
   https://github.com/join

2. Create a new repository:
   - Repository name: bates-courier (or any name)
   - Public repository
   - Add a README (optional)

3. Upload files:
   - index.html
   - style.css
   - README.txt (optional)

4. Enable GitHub Pages:
   - Go to Settings → Pages
   - Source: Deploy from main branch
   - Folder: root (/)
   - Click Save
   - GitHub will provide a URL like:
     https://yourusername.github.io/bates-courier/index.html

5. Test your app:
   - Open the link in a browser (PC or phone)
   - Fill out the form → check Google Sheet for submission

6. Optional mobile setup:
   - Open the link on phone
   - Tap Share → Add to Home Screen
   - Now your stores have an app-like experience
